{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Ban the use of PAVA Spray in UK prisons following its proven misuse in pilots",
        "additional_details": "Additionally we are calling for the Ministry of Justice to publish any safeguarding or training procedures relating to the use of the Section 5 weapon.\r\nPAVA Spray-a chemically concentrated version of pepper spray has been a controversial deterrent due to its \u00a32m rollout expense and its proven misuse in pilot trials. An analysis by the Prison Reform Trust (PRT) found that:\r\n24% of case studies involved unsafe use of PAVA\r\n34% of cases PAVA was used without justification\r\n24% involved use where alternative methods were available. Not as a \u201clast resort\u201d - which is the only acceptable time to be used according to the Ministry of Justice.",
        "background": "This petition calls for the UK government to ban the use of PAVA Spray following its proven misuse on prisoners during trials.",
